# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Custom domain for GitHub Pages — HOW TO USE THIS FILE
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GitHub Pages reads a file literally named `CNAME` (no extension) that
# contains ONLY your bare domain on a single line, e.g.:
#
#     mayaglbio.com
#
# This file is `CNAME.example` ON PURPOSE: an empty or malformed real `CNAME`
# can break Pages, so we ship the template instead. When you have a domain:
#
#   1. Copy this file to `CNAME` (same `docs/` folder), then DELETE everything
#      in it and replace it with just your domain on one line. No `#`, no
#      "http://", no path — just the host. For example:
#
#          yourdomain.com
#
#      (or a subdomain like `tools.yourdomain.com`)
#
#   2. Commit and push. GitHub: Settings -> Pages -> Custom domain will pick
#      it up (or set it there, which writes the `CNAME` file for you).
#
#   3. At your DNS provider, point the domain at GitHub Pages:
#        - Apex / root domain (yourdomain.com): add four A records to
#            185.199.108.153
#            185.199.109.153
#            185.199.110.153
#            185.199.111.153
#          (and optionally AAAA records for IPv6).
#        - Subdomain (www or tools): add a CNAME record ->
#            annomodtutorials.github.io
#
#   4. Wait for DNS to propagate, then tick "Enforce HTTPS" in Settings -> Pages.
#
# Until then, the site lives at:
#     https://annomodtutorials.github.io/maya-glb-io/
#
# replace with yourdomain.com
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
